This serious spontaneous report from a registered nurse concerns an 85-year-old male patient from the United 
States and was received on 27-MAR-2015.
The patient's relevant medical history included chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and no known allergies.  
The patient received 420 mg of IMBRUVICA (ibrutinib, capsule, oral) daily for the treatment of CLL.  The first dose 
of ibrutinib was initiated on 03-DEC-2014.  Concomitant medications included unspecified chemotherapy.
On (b) (6) , the patient was hospitalized due to the cough and wheezing and was diagnosed with hospital-
acquired pneumonia.  During the hospitalization, the patient was admitted to the telemetry unit for rapid ventricular 
response.  Treatment for the events included albuterol, two unspecified antibiotics, and steroids.  The patient's 
